5: All right. Everything seems to be in order.
13:
What are you still doing out here? 
Everyone's returned to their cabins 
already.
16:
Just making the rounds to make sure 
nothing's amiss.
22:
I'm merely ensuring that our voyage 
goes smoothly. 
It's about the most I can do these 
days.
25:
Doesn't it get tiring playing the role of 
the champion all the time?
26:
Have you ever thought of trying 
another way of life? You never know... 
It might just awaken something in 
you.
31:
Once again, I have no intention of 
becoming your pet, if that's what 
you're insinuating.
33:
I'm not looking to serve anyone or be 
served, for that matter. What I need 
are friends—companions that I can 
trust.
34: This is the only path I need to—
39:
...!
Why's the wind picking up all of a 
sudden?
63: I won't let that happen. Just trust me.
66:
Are you okay out there, Light? 
I thought you couldn't swim!
74:
I just jumped in without thinking and—
*glug* *glug*
78:
I can't BELIEVE someone could be so 
reckless!
81:
What do we do now, Aperio? 
They'll drown at this rate!
92: Is he afraid... because I'm afraid?
95: Aperio. Listen to me well, darling.
97:
Remember back to when I opened the 
grimoire for the first time. You were 
the first to answer my call, right?
99:
That's right—it was your bravery that 
led you to me. And I need you to be 
brave again right now!
118:
Thank you, Bianca. It was your quick 
thinking that saved us both.
122:
Oh, think nothing of it. It's what any 
pet owner would've done.
125:
A pet, huh? I could've sworn you called 
me a friend just earlier.
128: Surely you were just hearing things.
131:
I have no intention of becoming your 
pet, but a friend? I could do that.
134: Heh, cheeky little rabbit, aren't you?
138:
Hehe... I just hope that you'll keep an 
open mind. Isn't that right, Aperio?
